    "Additionally, it ascertains the supply and demand for sustainable practices in areas like investments (e.g., Cherrington et al. 2020; Dugo 2021; Duchin et al. 2022; Saetra 2022).",
    "Forecasting focuses on developing models to predict market movements, trends, volatility, anomalies, and events from an ESG perspective.",
    "This includes anticipating the consequences of environmental and social events, such as natural disasters and resource depletion, on financial markets.",
    "Furthermore, it entails forecasting the influence of CSR practices on financial performance and projecting the future effects of governance policies on market volatility.",
    "Predicting pricing, movement, supply, and demand within the energy market is also an integral part of this research area (e.g., Anas et al. 2020; Jabeur et al. 2021; Larsson and Ling 2021; Gao et al. 2022; Guliyev and Mustafayev 2022)."
